<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="235" pageId="1" pageNumber="234" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[810,1452,1035,2065]" lastBlockId="2.[136,778,1410,1614]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="235" pageId="1" pageNumber="234">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[863,1009,1465,1491]" pageId="1" pageNumber="234">Description.</emphasis>
Body 
<quantity box="[1087,1189,1465,1492]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.61" pageId="1" pageNumber="234" unit="mm" value="2.61">2.61 mm</quantity>
long (from head tip to abdomen); head 
<quantity box="[1002,1105,1501,1528]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.43" pageId="1" pageNumber="234" unit="mm" value="1.43">1.43 mm</quantity>
long; clypeus divided into an ante- and a postclypeus; antenna with 55 segments, 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.46" pageId="1" pageNumber="234" unit="mm" value="8.46">8.46 mm</quantity>
long; maxillary palp 
<quantity box="[1108,1211,1573,1600]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.15" pageId="1" pageNumber="234" unit="mm" value="2.15">2.15 mm</quantity>
long; apical sensory zone of maxillary palp elongate (
<figureCitation box="[1194,1284,1609,1635]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[136,235,831,855]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,171,807]" captionTargetId="figure-76@3.[151,1436,171,807]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Aenigmaraphidophora mouniri gen. et sp. nov., male, holotype BKT-3A. A, Head, lateral view. B, Apical sensory zone of maxillary palp. C, Tympan on fore leg. Scale bars = 1 mm in A and 0.3 mm in B and C." pageId="1" pageNumber="234">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
), much longer than palp apical width; thorax 
<quantity box="[1168,1271,1645,1671]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.7" pageId="1" pageNumber="234" unit="mm" value="0.97">0.97 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[1348,1452,1645,1671]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.2" pageId="1" pageNumber="234" unit="mm" value="0.92">0.92 mm</quantity>
high; four tarsomeres on all legs; fore leg with tibia 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="234" unit="mm" value="0.95">0.95 mm</quantity>
long, tarsus 
<quantity box="[1001,1088,1716,1743]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="234" unit="mm" value="0.4">0.4 mm</quantity>
long, distal articulation zone of fore coxa displaced laterally; tympan present on fore tibia (
<figureCitation box="[818,909,1788,1814]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[136,235,831,855]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,171,807]" captionTargetId="figure-76@3.[151,1436,171,807]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Aenigmaraphidophora mouniri gen. et sp. nov., male, holotype BKT-3A. A, Head, lateral view. B, Apical sensory zone of maxillary palp. C, Tympan on fore leg. Scale bars = 1 mm in A and 0.3 mm in B and C." pageId="1" pageNumber="234">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
); mid femur 2.53 long, with one inner and one outer relatively large movable apical spines, tibia 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.1" pageId="1" pageNumber="234" unit="mm" value="0.91">0.91 mm</quantity>
long, tarsus 
<quantity box="[993,1092,1859,1886]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="234" unit="mm" value="0.55">0.55 mm</quantity>
long; hind femur 
<quantity box="[1290,1389,1859,1886]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.06" pageId="1" pageNumber="234" unit="mm" value="2.06">2.06 mm</quantity>
long, with outer side without any chevron ridges, tibia 
<quantity box="[1353,1452,1895,1922]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.76" pageId="1" pageNumber="234" unit="mm" value="1.76">1.76 mm</quantity>
long, with longest apical spur slightly shorter than first and second segments of hind tarsi combined, hind tarsi laterally compressed, 1 
<superScript attach="left" box="[1067,1078,2003,2017]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="234">st</superScript>
tarsomere with one flat pulvillus, 2 
<superScript attach="left" box="[824,840,2038,2052]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="234">nd</superScript>
and 3 
<superScript attach="left" box="[907,921,2038,2052]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="234">rd</superScript>
tarsomeres with a widened pulvilllus; abdomen 
<quantity box="[136,246,1410,1437]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" pageId="2" pageNumber="235" unit="mm" value="1.25">1.25 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[337,433,1411,1437]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="2" pageNumber="235" unit="mm" value="1.3">1.3 mm</quantity>
high; no femoro-abdominal stridulatory apparatus observable; abdominal tergites without obvious process on dorsal surface; epiproct without posterior process; cerci 
<quantity box="[507,610,1517,1544]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.5" pageId="2" pageNumber="235" unit="mm" value="0.95">0.95 mm</quantity>
long, straight, bearing very long setae, but without any bulbous-like sensillae; subgenital plate with styles (
<figureCitation box="[567,655,1588,1614]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[136,235,1847,1871]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,916,1823]" captionTargetId="figure-125@3.[151,1436,916,1823]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Aenigmaraphidophora mouniri gen. et sp. nov., male, holotype BKT-3A. A, Hind leg. B, Hind leg. C, Male terminalia. Scale bars = 1 mm in A and B, 0.5 mm in C." pageId="2" pageNumber="235">Fig. 3C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
